We recommended that:
the management require all Departments/End-Users/Implementing Offices to prepare and submit their respective PPMPs using the prescribed format and within the designated deadline, as per Section 318 of R.A. No. 7160, to facilitate timely preparation and approval of the Municipality's Indicative APP for CY 2023;
the BAC Secretariat, based on the submitted and reviewed PPMPs, prepare the APP in the form prescribed by the GPPB, indicating therein among others, the mode of procurement to be adopted, schedule for each procurement activities, and contract implementation to ensure that its procurement activities are properly/adequately planned;
the management meticulously and judiciously plan the procurement methods and timelines for each procurement activity and contract implementation, as mandated by Section 7 of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184, to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of the procurement process;
the management  provide training and capacity-building programs for relevant personnel involved in the preparation of PPMPs and APP to ensure a thorough understanding of the requirements and guidelines set out in the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 and other applicable laws; and
the management establish a monitoring and evaluation mechanism to oversee the preparation and submission of PPMPs and APP, ensuring compliance with the stipulated timelines and guidelines, and addressing any deficiencies promptly.

