We recommended that management:
notify or issue a demand letter to the persons liable requiring the immediate settlement of disallowances;
in case of non-compliance with the demand letter, require the Municipal Treasurer to withhold the salaries or any amount due to the persons liable for the settlement of their liabilities, unless a request for installment payment was approved by the Prosecution and Litigation Office (PLO) of the Commission on Audit pursuant to COA Resolution No. 2017-021;
if persons liable have retired, separated or transferred, and fail to comply with the demand letter, initiate appropriate civil actions under Section 35 of Presidential Decree No. 1445, with assistance from the Provincial or Municipal Legal Officer, as applicable;
continuously monitor the progress of settlement efforts and follow up with the persons liable as necessary to ensure compliance with repayment; and
maintain documentation of all communication, demand letters and legal proceedings related to the enforcement of settlement.

